### Why the Visuals Matter
In this analysis, we look at how Director of Photography Greig Fraser used custom lenses to create that specific 'bokeh' effect. 

The technical precision in the opening sequence sets the tone for the entire film. We break down the color palette—focusing on the heavy use of amber and deep blacks—and how it compares to previous iterations of the character.
